 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Nov. 3: The rate of inflation declined marginally to 4.49 per cent for the week ended October 22 from 4.71 per cent in the previous week, mainly due to fall in prices of essential food items and industrial fuel. Manufactured products became costlier, though. The wholesale price index remained unchanged at previous week?s level of 197.7 points.

 New Delhi, Nov. 3: IBM chairman and CEO Samuel J. Palmisano, who is on a four-day India visit, today met Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and IT minister Dayandhi Maran and discussed with them the company?s plans for the country. 

 New Delhi, Nov. 3: Air-India?s Rs 40,000-crore fleet acquisition plan from Boeing would cross another hurdle next week when a high-powered committee headed by the former comptroller and auditor general C.G. Somiah vets it. After a meeting with civil aviation minister Praful Patel today, finance minister P. Chidambaram said the proposal would now go to the oversight committee.

 New Delhi, Nov. 3: The government?s gross market borrowing has gone up by 41 per cent to Rs 1,06,000 crore till October 28. It is scheduled to raise Rs 8,000 crore on November 8, PNB Gilts said in a report. The budgeted gross borrowing for this fiscal is Rs 1,78,467 crore.

